# ─── Public (embedded in the browser bundle; not secrets) ───
# Create a project at https://supabase.com → Settings → API
# Use the Project URL and the anon (public) key. RLS in Supabase protects your data.

PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key

# Copy to ".env" for local dev: cp .env.example .env
# Cloudflare Pages: set the same variable names in Project → Settings → Environment variables
# (build + production). Rebuild after changing; values are baked into client JS at build time for PUBLIC_*.

# Supabase Auth (dashboard): set Site URL to your production origin (e.g. https://wellnessfirstglobal.com)
# and add redirect URLs: http://localhost:4321/** and your production /app/** if using email links.

# ─── Public forms (contact, newsletter/interest, webinar interest) ───
# Default: use API (unset or any value other than mailto). Requires /functions on Cloudflare Pages.
# For local `astro dev` without Pages Functions, set:
# PUBLIC_FORM_MODE=mailto
#
# Cloudflare Pages: bind an optional KV namespace as FORM_KV to persist submissions (JSON per key).
# Project → Settings → Functions → KV namespace bindings → Variable name: FORM_KV
# Without KV, submissions still return 200 OK; only a short log line is written (no PII in logs).
# Test /api/* on a Preview or Production URL; local `wrangler pages dev` can conflict with the Astro
# + Cloudflare adapter output—use the dashboard build or a branch preview for end-to-end checks.
